      <body>
         <div type="document">
            <head>Ships used in the Burnside North Carolina expedition</head>
               
               
               <ab>The following list includes key vessels identified by their specific roles in the expedition:</ab>
            
               <div>
                  <head>Army Division Vessels</head>
               <ab>These vessels were purchased or chartered by the Army and were often smaller, shallow-draft ships suited for the North Carolina sounds. </ab>
               <list>
                  <head>Flagships &amp; Transports:</head>
               <item>New York: Flagship of the 1st Brigade (Gen. Foster).</item>
               <item>Northerner: Flagship of the 2nd Brigade (Gen. Reno).</item>
               <item>Eastern Queen: Flagship of the 3rd Brigade (Gen. Parke).</item>
               <item>Cossack: Side-wheel steamer used by the 2nd Brigade.</item>
               <item>New Brunswick: Side-wheel steamer used by the 1st Brigade.</item>
               <item>Guide (Admiral): Side-wheel steamer used by the 1st Brigade.</item>
               <item>George Peabody: Transported Belgier's Battery.</item>
               <item>Pocahontas: Steam transport; famously lost in a gale during the expedition.</item>
               <item>City of New York: Steam transport; wrecked at Hatteras Inlet.</item>
               </list>
               <list>
                  <head>Army Gunboats (Armed Propellers):</head>
               <item>Pioneer</item>
                  <item>Ranger</item>
                  <item>Hussar</item>
                  <item>Vidette</item>
                  <item>Zouave (Zouave sank during a storm at Hatteras).</item>
               <item>Lancer</item>
                  <item>Sentinel</item>
                  <item>Chasseur</item>
               </list>
               <list>
                  <head>Floating Batteries (Armed Barges):</head>
               <item>Bombshell</item>
                  <item>Grapeshot</item>
                  <item>Grenada</item>
                  <item>Shrapnel Rocket</item> 
               </list>
               </div>
               <div>
                  <list>
                     <head>Navy Flotilla (Gunboats)</head>
               <note>Commanded by Flag Officer Louis M. Goldsborough, these ships provided the heavy firepower for the attack.</note> 
               <item>USS Delaware: Flagship of the tactical commander, Stephen C. Rowan.</item>
               <item>USS Commodore Perry: Heavily engaged at Roanoke Island; hit 8 times by round shot.</item>
               <item>USS Hetzel: Withdrew temporarily after a hit below the waterline.</item>
               <item>USS Hunchback: Suffered engine damage from a direct hit.</item>
               <item>USS Southfield: Carried a detachment of the 99th New York.</item>
               <item>USS Louisiana: Extinguished a fire during the bombardment of Roanoke Island.</item>
               <item>USS Morse, USS Valley City, USS Underwriter</item>
                  </list>
               </div>
